Program: Outlook
Title: 06/02/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00n96bq
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 7 Feb 2012
As heavy artillery fire rocks the Syrian city of Homs, Matthew Bannister talks to a soldier who defected after being ordered to fire on anti-Government protesters. Also in the programme, as the countdown to the Olympic Games continues, and as part of our "Edible City" series, a Ugandan-Asian woman based in London, cooks a dish that reminds her of home. And we meet Thinlas Chorol, a young woman from Ladakh in the Himalayas who broke down barriers by becoming a trekking guide. Show less